cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about optimizing the dialogue policy of a spoken dialogue system using reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves empirical evaluation of a working dialogue system, which could place it in the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
